      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this application; model form adequacy addressed implicitly through output comparison results.",
      "rationale": "RANS k-omega SST turbulence model with Giersiepen power-law hemolysis damage model selected based on published literature consensus. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2; addressed through output comparison factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, boundary conditions, and geometric parameters documented with sources and uncertainty ranges; sensitivity to key inputs quantified.",
      "rationale": "Blood density (1056 kg/m³ ±0.5%), viscosity (Carreau-Yasuda parameters from literature with ±8% uncertainty), pump geometry from FDA-released CAD file. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for five key input parameters; hemolysis index sensitivity coefficients reported."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; single representative pump unit used for validation testing.",
      "rationale": "Validation testing conducted on single FDA generic pump unit. Unit-to-unit variability assessment not required at MRL 2. Sample representativeness documented in test protocol TP-CBP-2022-04."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
